CSS ->
    Cascading Style Sheet
    Use To Design our layout
    It is not a case sensitive
    It has pair of property(p) and value(v)

    Types ->
        1. Inline

            Those css which is applied on a tag using Style attribute


            Example ->
                <tag style="p:v;p:v;........"></tag>
        2. Internal

            Those css in which we put out style tag inside head tag and we write our css there

            Example ->

            <head>
                <style>
                    selector{
                        p:v;
                        .
                        .
                    }
                    .
                    .
                    .
                </style>
            </head>




        3. External

            In css we create a new file with extension .css we write our css inside that file
            and we link css file with our html
            using link tag

            Example ->

                first.css
                    selector{
                        p:v;
                        .
                        .
                    }
                    .
                    .
                    .


                index.html
                    rel => relation
                <head>
                <link rel="stylesheet" href="location/filename.css" >
                <head>


        selectors ->
            1. tagname
            2. classname
            3. id
            4. *(universal selector -> apply on all)



            /*

            comsdkfjsdfk
            */






